empty dir:

✅ Purpose

Temporary storage inside a Pod

🧠 Key Points
Created when Pod starts
Deleted when Pod is removed
Shared between containers in same Pod
📌 Use Cases
Cache data
Temporary files
Sharing data between containers

"A folder created for a Pod — used while Pod is alive — disappears when Pod dies"

🔹 Lifecycle (VERY IMPORTANT)
Pod starts → EmptyDir created (empty folder)
Containers use it → read/write data
Pod restarts (same Pod) → data stays ✅
Pod deleted → data gone ❌

🔹 Where is it stored?

By default:

Stored on Node disk (like /var/lib/kubelet/...)

Option:

Can be stored in RAM (memory) using medium: Memory

